Interface VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VBiUnboundMethod<C,A1,A2,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    C - the generic type of the the class of the unbound method, which is also the type of the class instance argument
    A1 - the generic type of the first argument after the class instance argument
    A2 - the generic type of the second argument after the class instance argument
    R - the generic type of the return value, with VoidR as a possibility
    All Superinterfaces:
    SupplementaryFunctionalInterfaces.TriFunction<C,A1,A2,R>, UnboundMethodInterfaces.BiFunctionUnboundMethod<C,A1,A2,R>
    Enclosing interface:
    VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VBiUnboundMethod<C,A1,A2,R>
extends UnboundMethodInterfaces.BiFunctionUnboundMethod<C,A1,A2,R>
    A "voidable" unbound methoid interface which takes, in addtional to an initial class instance argument, two arguments of any generic types <A1,A2> and returns a value of any generic type <R> including VoidR.

    Function objects of the following types may be converted to this type:

    1. BiConsumeUnboundMethod<C,A1,A2> -> VBiFunctionUnboundMethod<C,A1,A2,VoidR>
    2. BiFunctionUnboundMethod<C,A1,A2,R> -> VBiUnboundMethod<C,A1,A2,R>
    VBiFunctions made from BiConsumer<A1,A2> return voidR; VBiFunctions made from BiFunction<A1,A2,R> return objects of generic type <R>.

      • Methods inherited from interface UnboundMethodInterfaces.BiFunctionUnboundMethod

        applyWithClassInstanceAsFirstArg

      • Methods inherited from interface SupplementaryFunctionalInterfaces.TriFunction

        apply
